Get-vCloud

Get-vCloud is a Powershell function library for VMware's vCloud API.


Installation

1. Download the .ps1 (or zip file) from GitHub and place in the folder of your choice.
2. Import the functions using "dot-sourcing" like so:

	. .\vcloud-functions.ps1

3. Profit!


The Functions

Current "cmdlets" are:

Connect-vCloud
Delete-vCloudURI
Disconnect-vCloud
Get-vCloudCatalog
Get-vCloudNetwork
Get-vCloudOrg
Get-vCloudURI
Get-vCloudvApp
Get-vCloudvDC
Get-vCloudVM
Post-vCloudURI
PowerOff-vCloudVM
PowerOn-vCloudVM


HELP!

For help on using the functions:

	get-help <cmdlet>
